<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12019q"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12019q">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12019q"> 19(q)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> baptised at Rouen</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Quand Charles le Simple offrit au duc Rollon sa fille en mariage et la cession du duch&eacute; de Normandie &agrave; condition de rendre hommage au roi de France et de se convertir au christianisme, le Normand n&apos;h&eacute;sita pas et se fit baptiser en grande pompe &agrave; Rouen: ses compagnons l&apos;imit&egrave;rent. <br><font color="green">[When Charles the Simple offered duke Rollo his daughter in marriage and the transfer of the duchy of Normandy in return for paying homage to the king of France and to convert to Christianity, the Norman did not hesitate and he had himself baptized with pomp and circumstance in Rouen: his companions did likewise.]</font> <small> &Eacute;douard Schur&eacute;, <a name="ESLL" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ESLL"><cite title="source">Les Grandes L&eacute;gendes de France</cite></a> (1892) 170</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Although baptised, Rollo (died 927) seems to have preserved certain pagan customs. </mm> </dd></dl>
